column9: respectively. Although Y181C itself reduces EFV susceptibility by only 2-fold

column1: {'id': 'RT_POS98G_NNRTI'} A98G is a nonpolymorphic accessory mutation that reduces NVP susceptibility by ~5-fold and EFV susceptibility by about 3-fold. It has a weight of 1.0 in the Tibotec ETR genotypic susceptibility score.

{'id': 'PR_POS54TAS_PIMajor'} I54A/T/S are nonpolymorphic PI-selected mutations that occur almost exclusively in patients who have received multiple PIs. I54A/T/S are associated with reduced susceptibility to each of the PIs except DRV.

column1: {'id': 'PR_POS82A_PIMajor'} V82A is a nonpolymorphic substrate-cleft mutation selected primarily by IDV and LPV. It reduces susceptibility to these PIs and causes cross-resistance to ATV and NFV. When it occurs in combination with additional PI-resistance mutations it is also associated with reduced susceptibility to SQV and FPV.

column2: less often
